function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> occursin(uppercasefirst(word)[1:1], word), words)
end
```

This function uses `filter` to iteratively remove any word that does not start with a capital letter as compared to the first character of the word in uppercase. The `occursin` function is used to check if a substring (the first character in uppercase) occurs within the string, and `uppercasefirst` is used to ensure that the comparison is case-sensitive.
